parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle continues to roll despite applying the brakes
the ABS system makes a grinding or noise
the brake pedal becomes rock hard
the vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause poor visibility while driving, especially in rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work intermittently
the windshield wipers stop working without warning
the windshield wipers do not shut off when switched off
the windshield wipers stop in the middle of the windshield
the windshield wipers come on without application.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Frame and Mounting Hardware Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame and mounting hardware can cause the seat to collapse or break, leading to a loss of control while driving, increased risk of injury, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Creeping or creaking noise coming from the seat base
cracks in the metal seat base
broken or thin bolts holding the seat back
seat back collapse
seat bolts breaking while accelerating from a stop.
